## Prereqs
- Terraform >= 1.6
- AWS credentials configured (profile or env vars)
- Existing EC2 key pair name (for SSH) if needed


## Quick start
```bash
# 1) Clone and enter the folder
# git clone <your-repo> && cd aws-3tier-terraform


# 2) Initialize
terraform init


# 3) Plan (override defaults as needed)
terraform plan \
-var "project=cloudinfra" \
-var "region=us-east-1" \
-var "admin_ip=YOUR_IP/32" \
-var "key_name=YOUR_KEY_NAME" \
-var 'alert_emails=["you@example.com"]'


# 4) Apply
terraform apply -auto-approve


# 5) Access your app
# Copy the output `alb_url` and open in a browser
```


## Customization
- Replace the `user_data.sh` with your app bootstrap.
- Set `ami_id` to a custom AMI if you have one.
- Toggle RDS via `create_rds` and tune instance sizes.


## Clean up
```bash
terraform destroy
```


## Notes
- For prod, consider one NAT per AZ, HTTPS on ALB with ACM, WAF, SSM Session Manager (no SSH), and secrets in AWS Secrets Manager.

